<subSubSection id="D449460833F9E1AFD0F177D239B6E0A6" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph id="B7B39606DDC479EF4E0E3AB0C9B34D9C" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BC9F506A1809D7F7CBC0349D89EEE6C9" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Very distinct because of the leaf-like bracts folded to form a spathe around the very small calyx and small subglobose Capsules and the suppression of the peduncle by fusion with the petiole. The flared funnel-shaped corolla is also distinct.</paragraph>
